        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 11:56PM EDT by NWS Wilmington OH</headline>
        <description>At 1155 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was located over Beavercreek,
moving east at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Hail may cause minor damage to
vegetation.

Locations impacted include...
Interstate 71 at State Route 38, South Vienna, Selma,
Wright-Patterson Afb, Oldtown, Gladstone, Yellow Springs, South
Charleston, Midway, Greene County Airport, Overlook-Page Mano,
Lisbon, Lilly Chapel, Clifton, South Solon, Jamestown, Interstate 70
at State Route 56, London, Beavercreek, and Plattsburg.

This includes the following Interstates...
I-70 in Ohio near mile marker 44, between mile markers 54 and 61,
and between mile markers 66 and 81.
I-71 in Ohio between mile markers 70 and 87.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a sturdy building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 300 AM EDT for central and
west central Ohio.

To report hazardous weather conditions, go to our website at
weather.gov/iln and submit your report via social media, when you can
do so safely.</instruction>
